    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-04-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-04-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="553"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d553">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Sir <persName
                            type="to">Julian Pauncefote</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-04-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 5, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 71.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to apprise you of the
                    receipt of a letter from the Acting Secretary of the Treasury, of the 2d
                    instant, in which he states that the Treasury Department has received
                    information to the effect that two vessels have engaged in sealing during the
                    past season which do not seem to be entered either on the American or
                    British-Canadian list of vessels. The vessels are the <hi rend="italic">C. E.
                        Fox</hi>, which is reported to have secured 250 skins, and the <hi
                        rend="italic">Sea Lion</hi>, 2,200 skins.</p>
                <pb facs="0669" n="609" xml:id="pg_609"/>
                <p>In view of this information the Department will be glad to have you ascertain
                    from the Canadian Government whether or not these vessels entered at British
                    Columbia, and, if so, further particulars as to their catch, numbers of crew,
                    etc.</p>
                <p>I may observe that neither of these vessels is mentioned in the list transmitted
                    with your note of March 14 last.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
